description.narrative:
Some of the key accomplishments of the project include the following:
1. A National Forensic Laboratory Centre is established in Garowe;
2. A dedicated laboratory technicians including two senior diaspora experts (one finansied by Swedish funding) with the necessary equipment for forensic serology and forensic DNA analysis laboratory is in place;
2. For the reporting period, 63 GBV survivors were provided with comprehensive GBV services (medical, psychosocial services and legal aid at the Maato Kaal GBV one stop centre;
3. Sexual Assault Protocol and training manual was developed. Inter-sectoral/inter-ministerial trainings were conducted;
4. A training manual was developed for the police and prosecutors based on the needs identified;
5. Awareness raising was conducted by the community police in the CID on sexual assaults;
6. The Sexual Offences Act implementation plan was developed.
